Active Record has validations built in and you can use them to make sure you get the data you want or NO SAVING EVER!

validates :name, :presence => true

before_create hook fires once during the entire life of the AR object.  before_save hook happens before each time it's saved.

AR provides you with many opportunities to hook into moments in the lifecyle of db records (look them up!)

Read strong_parameters documentation to learn how it works.

DJANGO == RAILS for Python!

Make methods in controllers private to make sure tehy can't be routed to/accessed from outside the inner workings of the page